File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function inverse_jacobi_cd u m

 -- Function: inverse_jacobi_cd (U, M)
     The inverse of the Jacobian elliptic function {\rm cd}(u,m). For
     -1\le u \le 1, it can also be written
     (https://dlmf.nist.gov/22.15.E15DLMF 22.15.E15):

     {\rm inverse\_jacobi\_cd}(u, m) = \int_u^1 {dt\over
     \sqrt{(1-t^2)(1-mt^2)}}

     {\rm inverse\_jacobi\_cd}(u, m) = \int_u^1 {dt\over
     \sqrt{(1-t^2)(1-mt^2)}}


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function inverse_jacobi_cs u m

 -- Function: inverse_jacobi_cs (U, M)
     The inverse of the Jacobian elliptic function {\rm cs}(u,m). For
     all u it can also be written (https://dlmf.nist.gov/22.15.E23DLMF
     22.15.E23):

     {\rm inverse\_jacobi\_cs}(u, m) = \int_u^{\infty} {dt\over
     \sqrt{(1+t^2)(t^2+(1-m))}}

     {\rm inverse\_jacobi\_cs}(u, m) = \int_u^{\infty} {dt\over
     \sqrt{(1+t^2)(t^2+(1-m))}}


File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function inverse_jacobi_dc u m

 -- Function: inverse_jacobi_dc (U, M)
